# rethunk-git MCP (this workspace)

This project registers **rethunk-git** via [`.cursor/mcp.json`](.cursor/mcp.json) (local `bun src/server.ts`). Cursor supplies workspace roots at MCP initialize; do not rely on a fixed `cwd` in config.

**Tool / resource reference** — ids, `rethunk-git_*` names, `format` / JSON, resource URI, workspace-root order: **[docs/mcp-tools.md](../../docs/mcp-tools.md)**. **Operator runbook** — install, Cursor `mcp.json`, preset file, dev/CI/publish: **[HUMANS.md](../../HUMANS.md)** (not auto-loaded; open when you need specifics).

**Do not link or re-open `AGENTS.md` from this rule:** Cursor already injects project **AGENTS.md** as agent context. Duplicating pointers here adds noise.

## When to use it

Prefer **`rethunk-git_git_*`** and **`rethunk-git_list_presets`** over shell **`git status`** / ad-hoc loops for multi-root or preset-driven git state. Use resource **`rethunk-git://presets`** when the client supports MCP resources.

## When shell git is still fine

Commands the tools do not cover (e.g. `git diff`, `git cherry-pick`), or when MCP is unavailable after a failed reload.

If tools are missing: **reload MCP** or run **`bun install`** so `bun` resolves for `bun src/server.ts`.
